The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on digital curation of web corpora. The paper proposes a novel framework for estimating the parameters of web corpora, such as their composition and lexicon, which are important for NLP tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses unsupervised topic models and supervised genre classification, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of language models pre-trained on large corpora, which is a popular technique in deep learning (DL) and could make cs.DL (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with web corpora, which could be considered a sub-topic of cybernetics (cs.CY).
